Photon Controller API Operations

This document presents a snapshot of Photon Controller's API operations as a convenience for those without a connection to Photon Controller. The preferred method of viewing the API documentation is to go to one of the following URLs on your running Photon Controller instance. Replace IP-address with the IP address of your load balancer:

Authenticated: https://IP-address/api

Unauthenticated: http://IP-address:9000/api

By viewing the API documentation through one of these URLs, you can interactively explore the API, find information about all the operations, and see the code.

  • /auth

      • get /auth

        • Returns Authentication/ Authorization Info

        Response Class

        • Model
        • Model Schema
        Auth {
        endpoint (String, optional): Url of the Authentication Server Endpoint,
        port (Integer, optional): The Authentication Server Port,
        enabled (boolean): Flag that indicates if auth is enabled or not
        } 
        {
  "endpoint": "String",
  "port": "Integer",
  "enabled": "boolean"
}

  • /available

      • get /available

        • Indicates that the Photon Controller API on this host is available

        Implementation Notes

        This API does not require authorization. It is intended for use by a load-balancer to decide that a host is available to service API requests. The response has no data. Getting a response with HTTP status code 200 is sufficient to indicate the host is available.

        Response Class

        • Model
        • Model Schema

        Response Class

        ResourceList {
        items (List[Vm])
        }
        Vm {
        metadata (Map, optional): Custom metadata for the VM instance,
        sourceImageId (String, optional): The id of the source image to create VM from.,
        floatingIp (String, optional): The public accessible IP of the vm,
        cost (List[QuotaLineItem]): This property specifies the base cost of the entity. It's important to note that the actual cost may be different due to runtime parameters used in the creation of an entity. For instance, the base cost of an ephemeral or persistent disk is augmented with a capacity cost at runtime.,
        kind (String): kind="vm",
        attachedDisks (List[AttachedDisk]): Supplies this list of disks attached to the VM. During VM creation, this list contains the list of disks that should be created and attached to the VM. Persistent disks can be attached to the VM only after the VM has been created.,
        datastore (String, optional): The datastore the vm is located on.,
        attachedIsos (List[Iso], optional): The ISO list attached to the vm,
        tags (Set, optional): This property specifies the set of machine-tags attached to the entity,
        selfLink (String, optional): [Output Only] Server-defined fully-qualified URL for this resource.,
        flavor (String): This property specifies the flavor of the entity.,
        host (String, optional): The host the vm is located on.,
        name (String): This property specifies the project-scoped name of the entity.,
        state (VmState) = ['CREATING' or 'STARTED' or 'SUSPENDED' or 'STOPPED' or 'ERROR' or 'DELETED']: Supplies the state of the VM,
        id (String): [Output only] Unique identifier for the resource, generated by the server.
        }
        QuotaLineItem {
        unit (QuotaUnit) = ['GB' or ' MB' or ' KB' or ' B' or ' COUNT']: Item unit,
        value (double): Item value,
        key (String): Item key (e.g., vm.cost, vm.memory, etc.)

        flavor (String): This property specifies the flavor value (e.g., core-100, etc.) for the entity being described by an instance of this class.,
        kind (String): This property specifies the kind value (e.g., vm, ephemeral-disk, etc.) for the entity being described by an instance of this class.,
        capacityGb (int): This property is the capacity of the disk in GB units. When used in the context of attaching an existing disk, this property, if specified, must be valid, but is otherwise ignored.,
        name (String): name,
        state (String): This property specifies the state value (e.g., STARTED, STOPPED, etc.) for the entity being described by an instance of this class.,
        id (String): id,
        bootDisk (boolean): This property specifies that the disk is the boot disk for the VM.
        }

        workerCount (int, optional): The number of worker VMs in the cluster.,
        extendedProperties (Map): A table of extra properties describing the cluster: please see the documentation for the complete list.,
        slaveCount (int, optional): Deprecated, use workerCount instead ,
        otherVmFlavorName (String, optional): This is the name of the flavor used to make all the VMs other than the master (e.g. the workers).,
        errorReason (String, optional): When the cluster state is either FATAL_ERROR or RECOVERABLE_ERROR, this contains the reason for the error.,
        name (String): The name of the cluster,
        state (ClusterState): The cluster state,
        id (String): [Output only] Unique identifier for the resource, generated by the server.,
        projectId (String, optional): The id of the project that this cluster belongs to.
